    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-07T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-07T23:00:00-05:00" n="444"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d444">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6–849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hong Kong</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hopper</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hong Kong</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-08T13:00:00+09:00"
                            >June 8, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 8—9 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>317. On June 8 interview with officer Consulate General, Yeh Tu-yi, Democratic
                    League official, stated his intention go Shanghai June 10, join Lo Lung-chi and
                    Chang Lan,<note n="94" xml:id="d444fn94">Leaders of the Democratic
                        League.</note> proceed Peiping on invitation Mao Tse-tung. Purpose trip is
                    prepare for PCC<note n="95" xml:id="d444fn95">Political Consultative
                        Conference.</note> which now planned for early August. Yeh said Democratic
                    League hopes to be “bridge” between Chinese Communists and US and so change
                    Communists’ present anti-American orientation.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 317, repeated Shanghai 83, Nanking 32, Peiping unnumbered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hopper</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
